 ('BOTULISM','<001>BOTULISM<002> A food-borne illness caused by toxins produced by the anaerobic bacterium, Clostridium botulinum. Botulism attacks the nervous system and is usually fatal.<003>FOOD-BORNE DISEASES<004><005>BACTERIAL DISEASES; CLOSTRIDIUM PERFRINGENS; SALMONELLA; STAPHYLOCOCCUS FOOD POISONING; ESCHERICHIA COLI; STREPTOCOCCAL INFECTION<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>https://www.jcfswinnipeg.org/Uploads/PDF/Chefs-Terminology.pdf (accessed date: 10-27-17)','2017-10-27 15:35:26','2017-10-27 15:46:46','abram','abram',115,NULL);
