 ('KWEK-KWEK','<001>KWEK-KWEK<002>It is a famous Filipino street food made by deep-frying hard-boiled quail eggs that are covered with orange batter. This is usually served with a spiced vinegar-based dip and chopped cucumber on the side. Another street food similar to this is called Tokneneng which uses chicken or duck eggs instead.<003>STREET FOOD<004><005>BANANA CUSE; FISH BALLS; PORK BARBECUE; SISIG; SPICY CHICKEN FEET<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://www.filipinochow.com/street-food/ (accessed date: 11-7-2017)','2017-11-07 11:15:04','2017-11-07 11:15:04','abram','abram',141,NULL),
 ('PORK BARBECUE','<001>PORK BARBECUE<002>Pork Barbeque are marinated slices of pork and is a very popular street food in the Philippines.<003>STREET FOOD<004><005>BANANA CUSE; FISH BALLS; KWEK-KWEK; SISIG; SPICY CHICKEN FEET<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://www.filipinochow.com/street-food/ (accessed date: 11-7-2017)','2017-11-07 11:19:39','2017-11-07 11:19:39','abram','abram',142,NULL),
