 ('CAPERS','<001>CAPERS<002>It is used in meat balls, stews, meat pies, tartar steak, salads sauces and pickled herring.  Capers should not be cooked with the food, but added to the finished product (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>SPICES<004><005>ANISE; ASUETE; BASIL; BAY LEAF; BURNET; CARAWAY; CAYENNE PEPPER; CHERVIL; CHIVES; CINNAMON; CORIADER; CLOVE; CURRY; DILL; GARLIC; GINGER; HORSERADISH; JUNIPER; MACE; MARJORAM; MINT; NUTMEG; ONION; OREGANO; PAPRIKA; PARSLEY; PEPPER; POPPY; ROSEMARY; SAFFRON; RED PEPPER CHILI <006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-20 11:40:05','2017-11-20 14:31:50','abram','abram',283,NULL),
 ('CARAWAY','<001>CARAWAY<002>An herb that is added to the food during cooking.  It is used in fly bread, sauerkraut, beef stews, soup and candy.  Caraway seeds like anise and kummel give a popular liqueur its distinctive flavor (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>HERBS; SPICES<004><005>ANISE; ASUETE; BASIL; BAY LEAF; BURNET; CAPERS; CAYENNE PEPPER; CHERVIL; CHIVES; CINNAMON; CORIADER; CLOVE; CURRY; DILL; GARLIC; GINGER; HORSERADISH; JUNIPER; MACE; MARJORAM; MINT; NUTMEG; ONION; OREGANO; PAPRIKA; PARSLEY; PEPPER; POPPY; ROSEMARY; SAFFRON; RED PEPPER CHILI <006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-20 11:43:15','2017-11-20 15:51:44','abram','abram',284,NULL);
