 ('CHERVIL','<001>CHERVIL<002>An herb and member of the parsely family (Antriscus carefollum) native to Russia; has dark green curly leaves that have a parsley-like flower with overtones of anise and are generally used fresh (Fenix, 2000).  Fresh chervil is used in soup and salads.  Dried chervil is used for seasoning in sauces and roast lamb (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>SPICES<004>DRIED CHERVIL; FRESH CHERVIL<005>ANISE; ASUETE; BASIL; BAY LEAF; BURNET; CAPERS; CARAWAY; CAYENNE PEPPER; CHIVES; CINNAMON; CORIADER; CLOVE; CURRY; DILL; GARLIC; GINGER; HORSERADISH; JUNIPER; MACE; MARJORAM; MINT; NUTMEG; ONION; OREGANO; PAPRIKA; PARSLEY; PEPPER; POPPY; ROSEMARY; SAFFRON; RED PEPPER CHILI <006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Fenix, Michaela.Cooking with Filipino Chefs. Center for Culinary Arts-Manila. Anvil Publishing, Inc. c2000.; Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-20 11:53:36','2017-11-20 15:53:20','abram','abram',286,NULL),
 ('CINNAMON','<001>CINNAMON<002>Ground cinnamon maybe used 9in pastries, bread pudding, cakes, andies and cookies.  Stock cinnamon is used for preserved fruits, pickles and fruit soups, sweet potatoes and hot beverages.  Oil of cinnamon distrilled from broken bar is used for flavoring and also for producing medicine (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>SPICES<004>GROUND CINNAMON; STOCK CINNAMON<005>ANISE; ASUETE; BASIL; BAY LEAF; BURNET; CAPERS; CARAWAY; CAYENNE PEPPER; CHERVIL; CHIVES; CORIADER; CLOVE; CURRY; DILL; GARLIC; GINGER; HORSERADISH; JUNIPER; MACE; MARJORAM; MINT; NUTMEG; ONION; OREGANO; PAPRIKA; PARSLEY; PEPPER; POPPY; ROSEMARY; SAFFRON; RED PEPPER CHILI <006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-20 13:48:48','2017-11-20 15:57:06','abram','abram',288,NULL);
