 ('CLOVE','<001>CLOVE<002>Whole cloves are used in marinades, leg of lamb, red cabbage, game of all kinds, meat stews, soups, eels in beer, marinated herring, pickles and ustard fruits.  Ground cloves are used in fruitcakes, gingerbread, honey cakes, pepper cakes (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>SPICES<004>GROUND CLOVE; WHOLE CLOVE<005>ANISE; ASUETE; BASIL; BAY LEAF; BURNET; CAPERS; CARAWAY; CAYENNE PEPPER; CHERVIL; CHIVES; CINNAMON; CORIADER; CURRY; DILL; GARLIC; GINGER; HORSERADISH; JUNIPER; MACE; MARJORAM; MINT; NUTMEG; ONION; OREGANO; PAPRIKA; PARSLEY; PEPPER; POPPY; ROSEMARY; SAFFRON; RED PEPPER CHILI <006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-20 13:55:01','2017-11-20 14:37:16','abram','abram',290,NULL),
