 ('KITCHEN','<001>KITCHEN<002>It is an area or a room or part of a building equipped for preparing and cooking food and washing dishes.<003><004>HOT KITCHEN; COLD KITCHEN; BUTCHERING SECTION; PASTRY SHOP; STEWARDING SECTION<005><006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-20 16:43:39','2017-11-21 14:54:18','abram','abram',330,NULL),
 ('CHICKEN WINGS (CHICKEN PARTS)','<001>CHICKEN WINGS (CHICKEN PARTS)<002>Parts of the chicken which are considered white meat and can be found uncooked, fully cooked, breaded, and unbreaded. They can be marinated, barbecued or glazed, and seasoned with spicy and rotisserie flavorings. <003>CHICKEN PARTS (COMPOSITION AND STRUCTURE)<004><005>WHOLE CHICKEN; POULTRY HALF; BREAST; BREAST QUARTER; BREAST HALVES; DRUMMETES; WINGETTES; WING TIPS; LEG QUARTERS; LEGS; THIGHS; DRUMSTICKS; GIBLETS<006><007>Cooking<008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>Reyes, Ruth Estrada Javier. 2015. Culinary arts. Published by Unlimited Books Library Services & Publishing, Inc, Manila','2018-01-13 13:25:12','2018-01-27 12:04:28','tina','tina',966,'');
