 ('CHEF D`PARTIE','<001>CHEF D`PARTIE<002>He/she is responsible for maintaining high quality food production in his section and ensures that standard recipes and control policies are enforce (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>CHEF<004><005>CHEF GARDEMANGER; PASTRY CHEF; SOUS CHEF<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-21 15:11:17','2017-11-21 15:11:17','abram','abram',339,NULL),
 ('CHEF GARDEMANGER','<001>CHEF GARDEMANGER<002>In-charge with the cold kitchen and expected to regularly check conditions in the deep freezer, chillers and refrigeration area (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>CHEF<004><005>CHEF D`PARTIE; PASTRY CHEF; SOUS CHEF<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-21 15:15:30','2017-11-21 15:15:30','abram','abram',340,NULL);
