 ('STEWING','<001>STEWING<002>This is the slow cooking of food (simmering) in the smallest quality of water, stock or sauce in a pan with a tight fitting lid (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>COOKING METHODS<004><005>BAKING; BLANCHING; BOILING AND SIMMERING; BRAISING; DEEP FAT FRYING; GLAZING; GRILLING AND BROILING; GRATINATING; MARINATING; POACHING; ROASTING; SAUTEING; STEAMING<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-27 16:28:42','2017-11-27 16:28:42','abram','abram',410,NULL),
