 ('SALTING (MEAT PRESERVATION)','<001>SALTING (MEAT PRESERVATION)<002>25 grams of salt added per kilo of meat will stop the growth of putrefying bacteria (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>MEAT PRESERVATION METHODS<004><005>CANNING; COOKING; DRYING; FREEZING; SMOKING<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 10:32:31','2017-11-28 11:38:09','abram','abram',416,NULL),
 ('SMOKING (MEAT PRESERVATION)','<001>SMOKING (MEAT PRESERVATION)<002>Same procedure as drying followed by smoking generally using wood chipping (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>MEAT PRESERVATION METHODS<004><005>CANNING; COOKING; DRYING; FREEZING; SALTING<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 10:33:45','2017-11-28 11:40:10','abram','abram',417,NULL),
 ('BROWN STOCK','<001>BROWN STOCK<002>It is made from beef, veal or poultry and aromatic vegetables which are partly and lighly roasted in fat (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>STOCKS (COOKING)<004><005>FISH STOCK; VEGETABLE STOCK; WHITE STOCK<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 10:49:00','2017-11-28 10:49:00','abram','abram',418,NULL);
