 ('SMOKING (FISH PRESERVATION)','<001>SMOKING (FISH PRESERVATION)<002>it can be used to haddock, eel, trout, tuna, salt fish, salmon (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>FISH PRESERVATION METHODS<004><005>CANNING; DEEP FREEZING; DRYING; PICKLING; SALTING<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 11:39:36','2017-11-28 11:39:36','abram','abram',430,NULL),
 ('MEAT GLAZE','<001>MEAT GLAZE<002>It is a gelatinous reduction of brown stock.  This produced out of the gelatinous content of the bones used in preparing brown stock.  This stock is used to strengthen the flavor and consistency of sauces and other culinary preparations (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003><004><005>DEMI GLAZE SAUCE<006><007>Glaze de viande<008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 11:45:44','2017-11-28 11:45:44','abram','abram',431,NULL),
 ('DEMI GLAZE SAUCE','<001>DEMI GLAZE SAUCE<002>It is obtained by reducing a combination of equal quantities of espagnole and brown stock.  It is used with small brown sauces (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003><004><005>MEAT GLAZE<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 11:48:12','2017-11-28 11:48:12','abram','abram',432,NULL);
