 ('SAUCES (CATEGORIES)','<001>SAUCES (CATEGORIES)<002>It is considered the basic foundation of quality classical cooking.  A sauce is a fluid dressing for meat, poultry, fish, desserts and other culinary preparations, designed to add appearance, flavor and texture to the food (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003><004>COLD SAUCES; WARM SAUCES<005>STOCKS<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 11:54:33','2017-11-28 13:31:58','abram','abram',434,NULL),
 ('COLD SAUCES','<001>COLD SAUCES<002>These are served with both hot and cold foods and include various butter preparations that are often associated with shellfish (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>SAUCES (CATEGORIES)<004><005>WARM SAUCES<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 13:30:10','2017-11-28 13:30:10','abram','abram',435,NULL);
