 ('WARM SAUCES','<001>WARM SAUCES<002>They are served with all types of food.  they are derives from a few leading sauces that are used as a base for nearly all others (Reyes and Ronald, 2006).<003>SAUCES (CATEGORIES)<004><005>COLD SAUCES<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 13:31:19','2017-11-28 13:31:19','abram','abram',436,NULL),
 ('SAUCES','<001>SAUCES<002>It is considered the basic foundation of quality classical cooking.  A sauce is a fluid dressing for meat, poultry, fish, desserts and other culinary preparations, designed to add appearance, flavor and texture to the food (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003><004>BROWN SAUCE; CREAM SAUCE;  HOLLANDAISE SAUCE; TOMATO SAUCE; VELOUTE SAUCE<005>STOCKS<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 13:37:33','2017-11-28 13:46:52','abram','abram',437,NULL),
 ('BROWN SAUCE','<001>BROWN SAUCE<002>It is made from brown stock and brown roux and is used extensively in the preparation of all types of meat and poultry dishes (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>SAUCES<004><005>CREAM SAUCE; TOMATO SAUCE; VELOUTE SAUCE; HOLLANDAISE SAUCE<006><007>Espagnole<008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 13:40:10','2017-11-28 13:40:10','abram','abram',438,NULL);
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('CREAM SAUCE','<001>CREAM SAUCE<002>It is originally prepared from veal stock.  It is derived from milk and/or cream with the addition of white roux.  The sauce is used with all types of vegetables and creamed dishes, including soups, fish, poultry, dairy and mararoni products (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>SAUCES<004><005>BROWN SAUCE; TOMATO SAUCE; VELOUTE SAUCE; HOLLANDAISE SAUCE<006><007>Bechamel<008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 13:43:26','2017-11-28 13:43:26','abram','abram',439,NULL),
 ('TOMATO SAUCE','<001>TOMATO SAUCE<002>It is prepared from tomato products, white stocks, seasoning and roux.  It is used with various meats, poultry, fish, vegetables and macaroni dishes.  It is also used for producing other products with a tomato character (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>SAUCES<004><005>BROWN SAUCE; CREAM SAUCE; HOLLANDAISE SAUCE; VELOUTE SAUCE<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 13:46:03','2017-11-28 13:46:03','abram','abram',440,NULL),
 ('HOLLANDAISE SAUCE','<001>HOLLANDAISE SAUCE<002>It is considered a leading sauce because many of the drawn butter sauces are prepared in the same manner as basic sauces.  Other sauces are derived from hollandaise (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>SAUCES<004><005>BROWN SAUCE; CREAM SAUCE;  TOMATO SAUCE; VELOUTE SAUCE<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 13:48:49','2017-11-28 13:48:49','abram','abram',441,NULL);
