 ('VELOUTE SAUCE','<001>VELOUTE SAUCE<002>It makes use of chicken, veal or fish, but more often, chicken is the usual ingredient.  A violate is derived from the stock with the addition of light roux and is associated with the product from which it is derived (Reyes and Roldan, 2006).<003>SAUCES<004><005>BROWN SAUCE; CREAM SAUCE;  HOLLANDAISE SAUCE; TOMATO SAUCE<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Dick. (2006).  Introduction to Culinary Operations.  Paranaque City: AR Skills Development and Mangement Services, 2006.','2017-11-28 13:50:31','2017-11-28 13:50:31','abram','abram',442,NULL),
