 ('DOMESTIC TOURISTS','<001>DOMESTIC TOURISTS<002>They travel within their own country. They do not cross international borders.<003>TOURISTS<004><005>ADVENTURERS; EXTRINSIC TOURISTS; INTERNATIONAL TOURISTS; INTRINSIC TOURISTS; LONG-HAUL TOURISTS<006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>http://filestore.aqa.org.uk/subjects/AQA-4840-W-TRB-OGKTLTI.PDF (accessed date: 11-28-2017)','2017-11-28 15:16:34','2018-01-09 15:46:09','abram','abram',452,''),
 ('ACHARA / ATSARA','<001>ACHARA / ATSARA<002>It is a native pickles made from various fruits and vegetables steeped either in vinegar and spices or brine. <003>FILIPINO SIDE DISH <004><005>CARROT; ONION; PAPAYA; SINGKAMAS; VINEGAR<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Abiva, Cris C. A Quick Guide to Fiilipino Food & Cooking.Manila. Anvil Publishing, Inc. c2001','2017-11-28 15:22:48','2018-01-19 14:39:27','janice','abram',453,''),
 ('HISTORICAL SITES','<001>HISTORICAL SITES<002>An attraction known for its intrinsic historic or heritage value overseas.<003>BUILT ATTRACTION<004>AGUINALDO SHRINE; BARASOAIN CHURCH; Biak-na-Bato National Park; Luna House; MacArthur Landing Memorial National Park; Malinta Tunnel; Nagcarlan Underground Cemetery; Plaza Cuartel; Rizal Park and Shrine<005>CHURCES; LANDMARKS; PARKS; ZOOS<006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>https://lifestyle.mb.com.ph/2017/06/11/10-must-visit-historical-sites-in-the-philippines/ (accessed date: 11-28-17).','2017-11-28 15:49:09','2017-11-28 15:52:18','abram','abram',455,NULL);
