 ('CULTURAL LANDSCAPES','<001>CULTURAL LANDSCAPES<002>Spaces of rich natural and cultural diversity that are often perceived through the imaginative lens as spaces of fairy tales and fables (Kozak and Kozak, 2015).<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 10:36:05','2017-12-04 10:36:05','abram','abram',507,''),
 ('COMMUNITY-BASED TOURISM','<001>COMMUNITY-BASED TOURISM<002>It is a recognized sustainable alternative to traditional forms of tourism development. Because CBT is seen as having the potential to alleviate poverty among indigenous people, CBT is expected to develop in Vietnamâ€™s Central Highlands â€“ a mountainous area which is home to a variety of ethnic minorities (Kozak and Kozak, 2015).<003><004>TOURISM MANAGEMENT<005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 10:40:43','2017-12-04 10:43:56','abram','abram',508,''),
 ('FORESTRYâ€“BASED ECOTOURISM MANAGEMENT','<001>FORESTRYâ€“BASED ECOTOURISM MANAGEMENT<002><003>TOURISM MANAGEMENT<004><005>COMMUNITY-BASED TOURISM<006><007><008><009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 10:48:19','2017-12-04 10:48:19','abram','abram',509,'');
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('STAKEHOLDER PARTICIPATION','<001>STAKEHOLDER PARTICIPATION<002>Stakeholder participation is important for destination sustainability. The process involves stakeholder identification, which assists destination managers in identifying the salient stakeholders. Stakeholder involvement has to take place in the initial stage of the ecoâ€“tourism development process. It is important for the sustainable use of tourism destinations (Kozak and Kozak, 2015).<003>COMMUNITY-BASED TOURISM; FORESTRY-BASED ECOTOURISM MANAGEMENT<004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 10:52:11','2017-12-04 10:52:11','abram','abram',510,''),
 ('STAKEHOLDER MAPPING','<001>STAKEHOLDER MAPPING<002>It can be defined as â€œa type of stakeholder analysis that focuses on the assessment of a large number of actors linked together by various forms of relationships (Kozak and Kozak (2015). <003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 10:56:59','2017-12-04 11:29:07','abram','abram',511,''),
 ('TOURISM POLICY','<001>TOURISM POLICY<002>Its implementation can based on stakeholder mapping which contributes to the improvement of destination management. This helps to identify the main actors involved in the tourism development of any destination and the role played by each of them in this process, as well as the relations existing among them (Kozak and Kozak, 2015) .<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 10:57:24','2017-12-04 11:04:36','abram','abram',512,'');
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('DESTINATION MANAGEMENT','<001>DESTINATION MANAGEMENT<002>Puts in place programs and strategies that will spread the unique story of a particular destination. Thus, inviting more tourists and enhancing tourism in that particular region. It proves to be a key to success for tourism management, at large (Tourism management, 2016).<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:05:55','2018-02-20 17:36:16','abram','abram',513,''),
 ('STAKEHOLDER THEORY','<001>STAKEHOLDER THEORY<002>This theory emphasises the importance of considering the diverse actors involved in order to be able to achieve the set objectives (Kozak and Kozak, 2015) .<003>TOURISM MANAGEMENT<004><005>STAKEHOLDER ANALYSIS<006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:06:18','2017-12-04 11:10:41','abram','abram',514,''),
 ('STAKEHOLDER ANALYSIS','<001>STAKEHOLDER ANALYSIS<002>A method to understand a system by identifying its key actors or stakeholders and assessing their respective interest in the system in question (Kozak and Kozak, 2015).<003>TOURISM MANAGEMENT<004><005>STAKEHOLDER THEORY<006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:11:14','2017-12-04 11:16:32','abram','abram',515,'');
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('STAKEHOLDERS','<001>STAKEHOLDERS<002>The term \"stakeholder\" has its origins in the work of Freeman (1984; 1994) on strategic management of business organisations. According to this author, stakeholders are defined as â€œany group or individual who can affect or is affected by the achievement of the organisationâ€™s objectivesâ€ (Kozak and Kozak, 2015).<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:14:28','2017-12-04 11:14:28','abram','abram',516,''),
 ('STAKEHOLDER COLLABORATION','<001>STAKEHOLDER COLLABORATION<002>A process of joint decision-making among key stakeholders of an interâ€“organisational community tourism domain to resolve planning problems of the domain and/or manage issues related to the planning and development of the domain (Kozak and Kozak, 2015). <003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:20:04','2017-12-04 11:54:56','abram','abram',517,''),
 ('APPRECIATIVE INQUIRY','<001>APPRECIATIVE INQUIRY<002>It is a recent approach used in tourism research and has been identified as a new research tool for evaluating the contributions of rural tourism (Kozak and Kozak, 2015).<003>TOURISM RESEARCH TOOL<004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:33:42','2017-12-04 11:36:39','abram','abram',518,'');
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('RURAL TOURISM MANAGEMENT','<001>RURAL TOURISM MANAGEMENT<002><003>TOURISM MANAGEMENT<004><005><006><007><008><009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:34:12','2017-12-04 11:34:12','abram','abram',519,''),
 ('TOURISM RESEARCH TOOL','<001>TOURISM RESEARCH TOOL<002><003><004>APPRECIATIVE INQUIRY<005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:37:07','2017-12-04 11:37:07','abram','abram',520,''),
 ('RURAL TOURISM','<001>RURAL TOURISM<002>An important developmental agenda and is a strong and growing sector in the global tourism market. The protection of nature coupled with economic growth, improvements in the builtâ€“environment, and development of infrastructure are the most significant contributions of this sector. Rural tourism has become a major force in rural economic development and therefore deserves further investment (Kozak and Kozak, 2015). <003>TOURISM<004><005>CULINARY TOURISM; DARK TOURISM; ENCLAVE TOURISM; MEDICAL TOURISM; ROOTS TOURISM<006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:40:11','2017-12-06 16:47:02','abram','abram',521,''),
 ('SUSTAINABILITY','<001>SUSTAINABILITY<002>It has become a buzzword, and while it is widely used in the tourism industry, the meaning varies according to the user: it most often refers to sustainability of profit, occasionally includes an element of environmental friendliness and less frequently refers to socio-cultural sustainability, although technically the term includes all of these aspects (Kozak and Kozak, 2015).<003><004><005>SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT<006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:46:47','2017-12-04 11:46:47','abram','abram',522,'');
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('COASTAL AREAS','<001>COASTAL AREAS<002>Key elements of the tourism network in constant and complex  restructuring, and in turn play a key role in relation to their contribution as recipients of domestic tourist destinations mainly, as well as to the development at local and regional level, without forgetting the stress generated at the territorial level and uncertainty about their future (Kozak and Kozak, 2015).<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:51:10','2017-12-04 11:51:10','abram','abram',523,''),
 ('COLLABORATIVE TOURISM','<001>COLLABORATIVE TOURISM<002>The ideal tourism collaboration approach emphasises increasing the socioâ€“economic contribution of tourism to rural areas. This is effected by encouraging non-hierarchical and flexible partnerships between the governmental (the public) and non-governmental (business, community and voluntary) sectors, encouraging bottom-up development and effectively mobilising the local human, cultural and natural resources (Kozak and Kozak, 2015).<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Kozak, M., & Kozak, N. (2015). Tourism Development. Newcastle upon Tyne: Cambridge Scholars Publishing.','2017-12-04 11:56:08','2017-12-04 11:57:59','abram','abram',524,''),
 ('TOURISM EDUCATION','<001>TOURISM EDUCATION<002><003><004><005>TOURISM STUDIES<006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>','2017-12-04 13:16:17','2017-12-04 13:16:17','abram','abram',525,'');
