 ('CONTEMPORARY TOURISM','<001>CONTEMPORARY TOURISM<002>The period from 1950 to the present day, characterized by the rapid expansion of international and domestic tourism (Weaver and Lawton, 2014). <003><004><005>EARLY MODERN TOURISM; PREMODERN TOURISM<006><007>Modern Mass Tourism<008>LTM<009><0010>Weaver, David and Lawton, Laura. (2014).  Tourism management.  Australia: Wiley.','2017-12-05 11:59:44','2017-12-05 13:30:42','abram','abram',533,''),
 ('PREMODERN TOURISM','<001>PREMODERN TOURISM<002>Describes the era of tourism activity from the beginning of civilization to the end of the Middle Ages (Weaver and Lawton, 2014). <003><004>LEISURE CLASS; OLYMPIC GAMES<005>CONTEMPORARY TOURISM; EARLY MODERN TOURISM<006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Weaver, David and Lawton, Laura. (2014).  Tourism management.  Australia: Wiley.','2017-12-05 12:01:13','2017-12-05 13:33:58','abram','abram',534,''),
 ('GRAND TOUR','<001>GRAND TOUR<002>A form of early modern tourism that involved a lengthy trip to the major cities of France and Italy by young adults of the leisure class, for purposes of educatio and culture (Weaver and Lawton, 2014). <003>EARLY MODERN TOURISM<004><005>SEASIDE RESORTS; SPA RESORTS<006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Weaver, David and Lawton, Laura. (2014).  Tourism management.  Australia: Wiley.','2017-12-05 13:19:23','2017-12-05 13:19:23','abram','abram',535,'');
