 ('DIM SUM','<001>DIM SUM<002>Cantonese term denoting both a style of morning or midday meal (also known as yum cha) and the small dishes served at that meal to accompany tea. Steamed and fried dumplings, both sweet and sour, are among the best-known dim sum dishes.<003><004><005><006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://www.gourmettraveller.com.au/recipes/how-to/2017/11/the-a-z-of-cooking-terms (accessed 01/27/2018).','2018-01-27 14:14:18','2018-01-27 14:14:18','janice','janice',1192,''),
 ('ZUCCOTTO','<001>ZUCCOTTO<002>This is an Italian form of charlotte royale. In this dessert, triangles of sponge cake are placed in a bowl to form a shell for the filling. The filling consists of stiffly whipped cream which is studded with toasted almonds, hazelnuts, chocolate chips, and candied fruit. A final layer of cake is placed over this, and when well set, the dessert is inverted onto a platter to form a large dome, reminiscent of Florence Duomo.<003><004><005><006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://www.culinarysoftware.com (accessed 01/13/2018).','2018-01-13 15:51:44','2018-01-13 15:51:44','janice','janice',987,''),
 ('ROUX','<001>ROUX<002>A mixture of flour and fat used to thicken sauces, soups, and stews. Though usually made with butter, rouxs are also made with bacon or poultry fats, margarine, and vegetable oil. The mixture is cooked for a brief time to remove the raw taste of the starch from the flour. Longer cooking results in a darker color, which is favorable in Creole cooking where rouxs are cooked for long periods until they reach a dark brown color.<003><004><005><006><007><008><009><0010>http://www.culinarysoftware.com (01/13/2018).','2018-01-13 15:53:53','2018-01-13 15:53:53','janice','janice',988,'');
