 ('CUTLETS (FISH CUTS)','<001>CUTLETS (FISH CUTS)<002>A single-serving cross-section portion-sliced straight through the backbone of a whole, dressed, round fish. It is slightly thinner than a steak, usually measuring 12mm/1/2-inc thick, and most often cut from the section between the head and mid-body. Suitable to any medium sized round fish. Also known as darnes.<003>FISH CUTS<004><005>BUTTERFLY FILLETS; CHEEK; DARNES; DRESSED; FILLETS; GOUJONS; LOINS; PAN-DRESSED; PAVES; STEAKS; SUPREMES; TAIL; TRONCONC; WHOLE; WINGS<006><007>Cooking<008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>Reyes, Ruth Estrada Javier. 2015. Culinary arts. Published by Unlimited Books Library Services & Publishing, Inc, Manila','2018-01-13 16:27:18','2018-01-27 16:30:31','tina','tina',1000,'');
