 ('BUTTERFLY FILLETS (FISH CUTS)','<001>BUTTERFLY FILLETS (FISH CUTS)<002>Round fish are de-headed then filleted by cutting through the belly, gutting the fish, opening it flat then removing the backbone and smaller bones, leaving the two fillets on each side of the fish joined in a `butterfly` style. (Reyes, Ruth Estrada Javier. 2015)<003>FISH CUTS<004><005>CHEEK; DARNES; DRESSED; FILLETS; GOUJONS; LOINS; PAN-DRESSED; PAVES; STEAKS; SUPREMES; TAIL; TRONCONC; WHOLE; WINGS<006>FISH CUTS<007>Cooking<008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>Reyes, Ruth Estrada Javier. 2015. Culinary arts. Published by Unlimited Books Library Services & Publishing, Inc, Manila','2018-01-13 16:49:40','2018-01-13 16:50:09','tina','tina',1007,'');
