 ('LIVE POULTRY','<001>LIVE POULTRY<002>When selecting live poultry, choose those birds that are aler, healthy, well feathered and well formed. A sluggish- looking bird should not be purchased. They should have a good fat covering, free of tears, broken bones, bruises and blisters. <003>POULTRY <004><005>WHOLE POULTRY ; DRESSED POULTRY ; DRAWN POULTRY ; POULTRY PARTS<006><007><008><009><0010>Reyes, Ma. Corazon and Simon, Jocelyn. (2009). Food selection and preparation manual. Manila: Mindshpers','2018-01-16 14:07:34','2018-01-16 14:07:34','janice','janice',1008,''),
 ('WHOLE POULTRY ','<001>WHOLE POULTRY <002>This is similar to the form of the live poultry but is no linger alive. <003>POULTRY <004><005>DRESSED POULTRY ; DRAWN POULTRY ; POULTRY PARTS ; LIVE POULTRY<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Ma. Corazon and Simon, Jocelyn. (2009). Food selection and preparation manual. Manila: Mindshpers','2018-01-16 14:10:24','2018-01-16 14:10:24','janice','janice',1009,''),
 ('DRESSED POULTRY ','<001>DRESSED POULTRY <002>These are slaughtered birds that have been bled, defeathered. The head, feet and viscera are still intact. <003>POULTRY <004><005>DRAWN POULTRY ; POULTRY PARTS ; LIVE POULTRY ; WHOLE POULTRY<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>Reyes, Ma. Corazon and Simon, Jocelyn. (2009). Food selection and preparation manual. Manila: Mindshpers','2018-01-16 14:12:32','2018-01-16 14:12:32','janice','janice',1010,'');
