 ('TOURIST','<001>TOURIST<002>A person who travels from place to place for nonwork reasons.<003>TRAVELER ; VACATIONER ; VISITOR ; BACKPACKER ; EXCURSIONIST<004>VACATIONIST ; VOYAGER ; JOURNEYER<005>NOMAD ; ROVER ; WANDERER<006><007>SIGHTSEER<008>LTM<009>ENGLISH<0010>Goeldner, Charles R., Ritchie, J.R. Brent and McIntosh, Robert Woodrow (2000). Tourism: principles, practices, philosophies. New York: John Wiley & Sons.','2018-01-24 14:41:21','2018-01-24 14:41:21','chezka','chezka',1098,''),
 ('TOUR GUIDE','<001>TOUR GUIDE<002>A person employed to show tourists around places of interest.<003>ATTENDANT ; ESCORT ; ORGANIZER ; COMPANION ; CHAPERON<004>COURIER<005>AGENT<006><007><008>LTM<009>ENGLISH<0010>Goeldner, Charles R., Ritchie, J.R. Brent and McIntosh, Robert Woodrow (2000). Tourism: principles, practices, philosophies. New York: John Wiley & Sons.','2018-01-24 14:46:18','2018-01-24 14:46:18','chezka','chezka',1099,'');
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('TOUR OPERATOR','<001>TOUR OPERATOR<002>A company that specializes in the planning and operation of prepaid, preplanned vacations and makes these available to the public, usually through travel agents.<003>TOUR AGENCY ; TRAVEL AGENCY ; TOURIST COMPANY ; TRAVEL COMPANY<004>TOURISM FIRM ; TOURIST AGENCY<005><006><007><008>LTM<009>ENGLISH<0010>Goeldner, Charles R., Ritchie, J.R. Brent and McIntosh, Robert Woodrow (2000). Tourism: principles, practices, philosophies. New York: John Wiley & Sons.','2018-01-24 15:00:33','2018-01-24 15:00:33','chezka','chezka',1100,''),
 ('BAGNET','<001>BAGNET<002>It is a slap of Pork belly literally deep fried in its own fat, over and over to crispy perfected meaty chicharron. Then it is cut into manageable bite size pieces before taking its final dip into the boiler oil bath. They are served with spicy vinegar.<003>ILOKANO DISHES; ILOKANO FOODS<004><005>DINAKDAKAN; DINARDARAAN; DINENGDENG; IGADO; ILOCOS EMPANADA; PINAKBET; PINAPAITAN; PINIKPIKAN; POKI-POKI<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://ilokanostudent.blogspot.com/2017/05/top-10-must-try-ilokano-food.html','2018-01-24 15:30:00','2018-01-24 15:30:00','abram','abram',1101,''),
 ('DINAKDAKAN','<001>DINAKDAKAN<002>Ilokano version of Sisig. You boil a head of a pig and harvest everything except the bones from it that includes the nose, ears, cheeks, and the brains. Some add pork belly, torched thinly sliced pork skin to the mix. Sometimes thrown into the grill for some crispiness. And sometimes, it`s simply marinated in vinegar and calamansi and seasoned with onions, garlic, and salt.<003>ILOKANO DISHES; ILOKANO FOODS<004><005>BAGNET; DINARDARAAN; DINENGDENG; IGADO; ILOCOS EMPANADA; PINAKBET; PINAPAITAN; PINIKPIKAN; POKI-POKI<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://ilokanostudent.blogspot.com/2017/05/top-10-must-try-ilokano-food.html','2018-01-24 15:34:28','2018-01-24 15:58:14','abram','abram',1102,'');
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('DINARDARAAN','<001>DINARDARAAN<002>This delicious meat dish is basically sauteed pork meat cooked pork blood with vinegar added to it. The consistency and color after cooking look like chocolate.<003>ILOKANO DISHES; ILOKANO FOODS<004><005>BAGNET; DINAKDAKAN; DINARDARAAN; DINENGDENG; IGADO; ILOCOS EMPANADA; PINAKBET; PINAPAITAN; PINIKPIKAN; POKI-POKI<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://ilokanostudent.blogspot.com/2017/05/top-10-must-try-ilokano-food.html','2018-01-24 16:02:13','2018-01-24 16:02:13','abram','abram',1103,''),
 ('DINENGDENG','<001>DINENGDENG<002>Refreshing Bean Soup dish. This soup is made with variety of green veggies cook with bagoong (fish sauce) and serve with grilled or fried fish like galunggong (roundscad), tilapia or bangus (milkfish).<003>ILOKANO DISHES; ILOKANO FOODS<004><005>BAGNET; DINAKDAKAN; DINARDARAAN; IGADO; ILOCOS EMPANADA; PINAKBET; PINAPAITAN; PINIKPIKAN; POKI-POKI<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://ilokanostudent.blogspot.com/2017/05/top-10-must-try-ilokano-food.html','2018-01-24 16:05:00','2018-01-24 16:05:00','abram','abram',1104,''),
 ('IGADO','<001>IGADO<002>It is a popular Ilokano dish that mostly made of liver, meat strips and sometimes other organ parts. The name comes from the Spanish word \"Higado,\" which translate to \"liver.\" Hence the part where it has to have liver in the ingredients. It`s cooked with bell pepper, peas, and carrots.<003>ILOKANO DISHES; ILOKANO FOODS<004><005>BAGNET; DINAKDAKAN; DINARDARAAN; DINENGDENG; ILOCOS EMPANADA; PINAKBET; PINAPAITAN; PINIKPIKAN; POKI-POKI<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://ilokanostudent.blogspot.com/2017/05/top-10-must-try-ilokano-food.html','2018-01-24 16:07:15','2018-01-24 16:07:15','abram','abram',1105,'');
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('ILOCOS EMPANADA','<001>ILOCOS EMPANADA<002>These empanadas are orange! They mix achuete/annatto powder into their batter flour for flavor and color. The filling consist of shredded papaya or beans sprout with eggs and sometimes longganisa sausage. They are deep fried and dipped in spicy vinegar.<003>ILOKANO DISHES; ILOKANO FOODS<004><005>BAGNET; DINAKDAKAN; DINARDARAAN; DINENGDENG; IGADO; PINAKBET; PINAPAITAN; PINIKPIKAN; POKI-POKI<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://ilokanostudent.blogspot.com/2017/05/top-10-must-try-ilokano-food.html','2018-01-24 16:09:01','2018-01-24 16:09:01','abram','abram',1106,''),
 ('PINAKBET','<001>PINAKBET<002>It is a combination of vegetables cooked in bagoong (fish sauce). Bagnet is a perfect addition to this dish but some prefer to put shrimp. I used to wonder why my mom always has bittermelon, eggplant, okra, kabocha squash, and long beans in her garden.<003>ILOKANO DISHES; ILOKANO FOODS<004><005>BAGNET; DINAKDAKAN; DINARDARAAN; DINENGDENG; IGADO; ILOCOS EMPANADA; PINAPAITAN; PINIKPIKAN; POKI-POKI<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://ilokanostudent.blogspot.com/2017/05/top-10-must-try-ilokano-food.html','2018-01-24 16:11:45','2018-01-24 16:11:45','abram','abram',1107,''),
 ('PINAPAITAN','<001>PINAPAITAN<002>Pinapaitan stems from the word \"Pait,\" which means bitter. Have you heard of Mexican Menudo?  It is much the same soup dish. The difference is in the seasoning. Pinapaitan is an Ilokano soup dish that is mostly made with cow or goat innards and seasoned in its bile extract.<003>ILOKANO DISHES; ILOKANO FOODS<004><005>BAGNET; DINAKDAKAN; DINARDARAAN; DINENGDENG; IGADO; ILOCOS EMPANADA; PINAKBET; PINIKPIKAN; POKI-POKI<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://ilokanostudent.blogspot.com/2017/05/top-10-must-try-ilokano-food.html','2018-01-24 16:16:09','2018-01-24 16:16:09','abram','abram',1108,'');
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('PINIKPIKAN','<001>PINIKPIKAN<002>An Igorot delicacy. This is a chicken soup dish that is best made with \"native\" chicken or a mountain/wild chicken. The native chicken has long since been domesticated but still, it just tastes different. They have a darker meat and gamier taste. The feathers of the chicken are roasted off over open fire leaving the skin a bit torched but flavorful. It`s cook for a long time to tenderize the meat and seasoned with ginger and fish sauce. Some add papaya or pepper leaves to have a bit of veggie option.<003>ILOKANO DISHES; ILOKANO FOODS<004><005>BAGNET; DINAKDAKAN; DINARDARAAN; DINENGDENG; IGADO; ILOCOS EMPANADA; PINAKBET; PINAPAITAN; POKI-POKI<006><007><008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://ilokanostudent.blogspot.com/2017/05/top-10-must-try-ilokano-food.html','2018-01-24 16:23:56','2018-01-24 16:23:56','abram','abram',1109,''),
 ('POKI-POKI','<001>POKI-POKI<002>It is grilled eggplant salad. Much like Tortang Talong except it has eggs and onions. Eggplants are grilled until the skin puff out then the toasty skin is removed. Then the mashed eggplants are pan-fried with scrambled eggs, onions and diced tomatoes. Eat dipped in soy sauce or fish sauce.<003>ILOKANO DISHES; ILOKANO FOODS<004><005>BAGNET; DINAKDAKAN; DINARDARAAN; DINENGDENG; IGADO; ILOCOS EMPANADA; PINAKBET; PINAPAITAN; PINIKPIKAN<006><007>Poqui-Poqui<008>Culinary Arts<009><0010>http://ilokanostudent.blogspot.com/2017/05/top-10-must-try-ilokano-food.html','2018-01-24 16:25:57','2018-01-24 16:25:57','abram','abram',1110,'');
