 ('TENDERLOINS (CHICKEN PARTS)','<001>TENDERLOINS (CHICKEN PARTS)<002>The muscle of the breast, which runs along both sides of the breastbone, located on the upper portion of the breast. Consists of white meat only.<003>CHICKEN PARTS (COMPOSITION AND STRUCTURE)<004><005>WHOLE CHICKEN; POULTRY HALF; BREAST; BREAST QUARTER; BREAST HALVES; WINGS; DRUMMETES; WINGETTES; WING TIPS; LEG QUARTERS; LEGS; THIGHS; DRUMSTICKS; GIBLETS<006><007>Cooking<008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>http://www.recipetips.com/kitchen-tips/t--365/chicken-description-of-parts.asp. Retrieved January 27, 2018.','2018-01-27 10:44:43','2018-01-27 10:44:43','tina','tina',1179,''),
