 ('PRIMATE TOURISM','<001>PRIMATE TOURISM<002>The use of nonhuman primates as the focus of tourism, with the aim of generating revenue and making conservation of primates and habitat worthwhile to local human populations. In practice, this oft-touted conservation tool has been riddled with problems, calling into question whether it is helping or hurting conservation. Safari-like primate tourism excursions, mainly focused on great apes, have shown the greatest efforts to manage tourism to limit negative impacts on primates, and are characterized here on the â€œhigh responsibilityâ€ end of an ecotourism spectrum. Nevertheless, there are still considerable problems, including compliance with adopted guidelines, and disease transmission. Monkey forests fall toward the â€œlow responsibilityâ€ end of the spectrum, and show the most issues with habitat destruction and escalating aggression.<003>TOURISM; NATURE-BASED TOURISM<004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/9781119179313.wbprim0241/abstract?systemMessage=Please+be+advised+that+we+experienced+an+unexpected+issue+that+occurred+on+Saturday+and+Sunday+January+20th+and+21st+that+caused+the+site+to+be+down+for+an+extended+period+of+time+and+affected+the+ability+of+users+to+access+content+on+Wiley+Online+Library.+This+issue+has+now+been+fully+resolved.++We+apologize+for+any+inconvenience+this+may+have+caused+and+are+working+to+ensure+that+we+can+alert+you+immediately+of+any+unplanned+periods+of+downtime+or+disruption+in+the+future. (Accessed date: 2/1/2018).','2018-02-01 14:58:31','2018-02-01 14:58:31','abram','abram',1252,'');
INSERT INTO `pantasdb`.`thesaurus` (`title`,`maintext`,`date_entered`,`date_updated`,`entered_by`,`updated_by`,`id`,`image_location`) VALUES 
 ('FILM-INDUCED TOURISM','<001>FILM-INDUCED TOURISM<002>Place or location used as film sites in the hope of attracting and promoting tourism destinations.<003>TOURISM<004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>Beeton, S. (2016). Film-Induced Tourism. Clevedon: Channel View Publications.','2018-02-01 15:20:57','2018-02-01 15:20:57','abram','abram',1253,''),
 ('ACCULTURATION','<001>ACCULTURATION<002>It is the process of cultural and psychological change that takes place as a result of contact between cultural groups and their individual members. Such contact and change occur during colonization, military invasion, migration, and sojourning (e.g., tourism, international study, overseas posting).<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009><0010>J.W. Berry, in Encyclopedia of Applied Psychology, 2004','2018-02-01 16:15:21','2018-02-01 16:15:21','abram','abram',1254,''),
 ('ACTION RESEARCH','<001>ACTION RESEARCH<002>It involves an approach which is compatible with learning organisations, and the development of a culture of permanent improvement. For hospitality management educators action research represents both a technique to include in the development of hospitality managers, and a technique which can inform the improvement of their own professional practice.<003><004><005><006><007><008><009><0010>Lashley, Conrdad. (2000). Action Research: An Essential Tool for Hospitality Management Education? Tourism and Hospitality Research Vol 1, Issue 4, pp. 313 - 327.','2018-02-01 16:22:55','2018-02-01 16:22:55','abram','abram',1255,'');
