 ('ANIMATION','<001>ANIMATION<002>Form of care to guests or tourists with the aim of fostering their behavior and enticing enthusiasm for certain touristic activities in order to promote specific experiences.<003><004><005><006><007><008><009><0010>Encyclopedia of tourism. (2000).  London: Routledge.','2018-02-02 16:37:31','2018-02-02 16:37:31','abram','abram',1260,''),
 ('ZEST','<001>ZEST<002>To remove the outermost skin layers of citrus fruit using a knife, peeler or zester. When zesting, be careful not to remove the pith, the white layer between the zest and the flesh, which is bitter.<003><004><005><006><007><008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>https://mymission.lamission.edu/userdata/higginaa/docs/culinary%20terms%202016.pdf. Retrieved February 3, 2017','2018-02-03 13:54:37','2018-02-03 13:54:37','tina','tina',1261,''),
 ('ZAHTAR','<001>ZAHTAR<002>A Middle Eastern spice blend composed of ground driedÂ thyme,Â oregano,Â marjoram, or some combination thereof, mixed withÂ toastedÂ sesame seeds, andÂ salt, and other spices such asÂ sumacÂ <003><004><005><006><007>Culinary<008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>https://mymission.lamission.edu/userdata/higginaa/docs/culinary%20terms%202016.pdf. Retrieved February 3, 2017','2018-02-03 14:03:35','2018-02-03 14:03:35','tina','tina',1262,'');
