 ('YAKITORI','<001>YAKITORI<002>It is a Japanese dish of bite-sized pieces of chicken that are skewered and roasted over a grill, typically a charcoal grill.<003><004><005><006><007>Grilling<008>Culinary arts<009>Japanese<0010>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yakitori. Retrieved February 3, 2018','2018-02-03 14:21:57','2018-02-08 16:25:38','tina','abram',1263,''),
 ('PAUPIETTE','<001>PAUPIETTE<002>A paupiette /pauÂ·piette/ is a piece of meat, beaten thin, and rolled with a stuffing of vegetables, fruits or sweetmeats. It is often featured in recipes from Normandy. It is often fried or braised, or baked in wine or stock. Also known as roulade /<003><004><005>ROULADE<006><007><008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>https://pos.toasttab.com/blog/culinary-terms. Retrieved February 3, 2018','2018-02-03 14:31:43','2018-02-03 14:31:43','tina','tina',1264,''),
 ('GALANTINE (DISH)','<001>GALANTINE (DISH)<002>A galantine is a French dish of de-boned stuffed meat, most commonly poultry or fish, that is poached and served cold, coated with aspic. Galantines are often stuffed with forcemeat, and pressed into a cylindrical shape.<003><004><005><006><007>DISH<008>Culinary arts<009>English, French<0010>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galantine. Retrieved February 3, 2018','2018-02-03 14:35:32','2018-02-03 14:35:32','tina','tina',1265,'');
