 ('HAZARD ANALYSIS CRITICAL CONTROL POINT (HACCP)','<001>HAZARD ANALYSIS CRITICAL CONTROL POINT (HACCP)<002>A food safety system of self-inspection designed to highlight hazardous foods and to control food handling with the gal of avoiding hazards.<003><004><005><006><007><008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>Gisslen, Wayne. Essentials of professional cooking. Â©2016 Published by John Wiley & Sons, Inc. , Hoboken, New Jersey','2018-02-06 14:38:57','2018-02-06 14:38:57','tina','tina',1328,''),
 ('WIRE WHIP','<001>WIRE WHIP<002>A hand tool or mixer attachment used for whipping tasks, such as beating cream and eggs and makingmayonnaise.<003><004><005><006><007><008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>Gisslen, Wayne. Essentials of professional cooking. Â©2016 Published by John Wiley & Sons, Inc. , Hoboken, New Jersey','2018-02-06 14:42:45','2018-02-06 14:42:45','tina','tina',1329,''),
 ('WRAP (FOOD)','<001>WRAP (FOOD)<002>Is made with a softÂ flatbreadÂ rolled around a filling. The usual flatbreads areÂ wheat tortillas,Â lavash, orÂ pita; the filling usually consists of cold sliced meat, poultry, or fish accompanied by shreddedÂ lettuce, diced tomato orÂ pico de gallo,Â guacamole, sauteedÂ mushrooms,Â bacon, grilledÂ onions,Â cheese, and aÂ sauce, such asÂ ranchÂ orÂ honey mustard.<003><004><005><006><007><008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wrap_(food). Retrieved February 6, 2018','2018-02-06 14:48:44','2018-02-06 14:48:44','tina','tina',1330,'');
