 ('TEXTURED VEGETABLE PROTEIN (TVP)','<001>TEXTURED VEGETABLE PROTEIN (TVP)<002>Textured or texturized vegetable protein, also known as textured soy protein, soy meat, or soya chunks is a defatted soy flour product, a by-product of extracting soybean oil. It is often used as a meat analogue or meat extender. (Wikipedia. Retrieved February 6, 2018)<003><004><005><006><007><008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>Gisslen, Wayne. Essentials of professional cooking. Â©2016 Published by John Wiley & Sons, Inc. , Hoboken, New Jersey','2018-02-06 15:14:27','2018-02-06 15:14:27','tina','tina',1332,''),
 ('MAYONNAISE','<001>MAYONNAISE<002>A semisolid cold sauce or dressing consisting of oil and vinegar emulsified with egg yolks.<003>SALAD DRESSING<004><005><006><007><008>Culinary arts<009>English<0010>Gisslen, Wayne. Essentials of professional cooking. Â©2016 Published by John Wiley & Sons, Inc. , Hoboken, New Jersey','2018-02-06 15:39:31','2018-02-06 15:39:31','tina','tina',1333,'');
