 ('NATIONAL TOURISM POLICY ACT of 1981','<001>NATIONAL TOURISM POLICY ACT of 1981<002>This act redefined the national interest in tourism and created the United States Travel and Tourism Administration (USTTA), replacing the United States Travel Service as the nation`s government tourism office.<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009>ENGLISH<0010>Walker, John R. and Walker, Josielyn T. (2011). Tourism: concepts and practices. Boston: Prentice Hall.','2018-02-15 11:40:03','2018-02-15 11:40:03','chezka','chezka',1440,''),
 ('NATIONAL TOURIST OFFICE','<001>NATIONAL TOURIST OFFICE<002>An organization designed to promote travel and tourism to and within the country it represents.<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009>ENGLISH<0010>Walker, John R. and Walker, Josielyn T. (2011). Tourism: concepts and practices. Boston: Prentice Hall.','2018-02-15 11:40:19','2018-02-15 11:40:19','chezka','chezka',1441,''),
 ('OFFICE OF TRAVEL AND TOURISM INDUSTRIES','<001>OFFICE OF TRAVEL AND TOURISM INDUSTRIES<002>The United States` national tourism office for research and policy issues. As part of the U.S. Department of Commerce, International Trade Administration, OTTI is mandated to develop, collect, and report the necessary statistical and market research on international travel to facilitate and guide planning in the public and private sectors.<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009>ENGLISH<0010>Walker, John R. and Walker, Josielyn T. (2011). Tourism: concepts and practices. Boston: Prentice Hall.','2018-02-15 11:40:53','2018-02-15 11:40:53','chezka','chezka',1442,'');
