 ('ROUTE 66','<001>ROUTE 66<002>A historic highway that goes from Chicago, Illinois, through eight states to end in Santa Monica, California. This route is also called \"The Highway of Hope.\"<003><004><005><006><007><008>LTM<009>ENGLISH<0010>Walker, John R. and Walker, Josielyn T. (2011). Tourism: concepts and practices. Boston: Prentice Hall.','2018-02-15 11:43:22','2018-02-15 11:43:22','chezka','chezka',1449,''),
 ('SCENIC TRIP','<001>SCENIC TRIP<002>A road or part of a stretch of road that offers spectacular views.<003>EYE-CATCHING ; STUNNING ; STRIKING ; FABULOUS ; SPLENDID ; SUPERB ; MAGNIFICENT ; IMPRESSIVE<004>DAZZLING ; ASTOUNDING ; ASTONISHING ; AMAZING ; DRAMATIC ; WONDERFUL<005><006><007><008>LTM<009>ENGLISH<0010>Walker, John R. and Walker, Josielyn T. (2011). Tourism: concepts and practices. Boston: Prentice Hall.','2018-02-15 11:44:49','2018-02-15 11:44:49','chezka','chezka',1450,'');
